1
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:14,067
We'll get out of here, okay?
We'll get out of here.

2
00:00:14,133 --> 00:00:15,867
- Emma!
- Which key is it?

3
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:18,067
Help me bring this trash out!
Hurry!

4
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:19,467
Ma'am Astrid!

5
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:21,800
I know you're not as evil
as your friend.

6
00:00:21,867 --> 00:00:23,833
Don't tell me Emma
was telling the truth?

7
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,967
That Mookie needs my help?

8
00:00:26,033 --> 00:00:27,700
I'll help you with Mookie,
but...

9
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:29,367
but let's go home for now.

10
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:31,367
I'm just concerned
about the kid.

11
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:33,200
I don't want her
to get harmed, too.

12
00:00:38,867 --> 00:00:39,700
Mom, where's Emma?

13
00:00:39,767 --> 00:00:40,967
Why are you looking for Emma?

14
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:43,367
I saw you went into the room
together.

15
00:00:43,433 --> 00:00:44,567
Looks like she left.

16
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:46,800
I have the keys
to Ma'am Olive's house.

17
00:00:46,867 --> 00:00:48,300
We can get inside.

18
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:55,400
Mookie!

19
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,300
Mookie!

20
00:01:58,367 --> 00:02:00,467
Mookie, please don't leave me.

21
00:02:02,167 --> 00:02:04,833
Mookie, sweetie.
I know you're just around.

22
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:05,900
Please.

23
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,633
Mookie, please.

24
00:02:10,267 --> 00:02:12,633
Please, Mookie, don't leave me.

25
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:19,900
Didn't I promise I'd care
for you no matter what happens?

26
00:02:19,967 --> 00:02:22,233
And you also made a promise
to me!

27
00:02:25,167 --> 00:02:28,433
You promised me
you wouldn't leave me, right?

28
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:29,600
Mookie!

29
00:02:33,967 --> 00:02:35,167
Mookie, please!

30
00:02:35,233 --> 00:02:39,167
I'm begging you, Mookie.

31
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:41,567
Don't leave mommy, Mookie.

32
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,433
Didn't you say...

33
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:50,733
didn't you say you wanted
to be a doctor like mommy?

34
00:02:52,933 --> 00:02:55,633
You said you'd treat me...

35
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,500
when I get sick, right?

36
00:02:59,300 --> 00:03:00,800
Please, Mookie.

37
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:05,067
You're the only one I have,
Mookie!

38
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:07,300
Mookie?

39
00:03:09,267 --> 00:03:10,800
Mookie, please!

40
00:03:10,867 --> 00:03:13,067
Where are you, Dear?

41
00:03:13,133 --> 00:03:15,767
I promise I will be good to you.

42
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:17,567
Mookie, please!

43
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:19,800
Just don't leave me.

44
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:28,633
I knew it!

45
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,367
Mommy...

46
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:32,833
Where do you think you're going?

47
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,700
Let's come home, Mookie.

48
00:03:34,767 --> 00:03:36,200
No, Mommy.

49
00:03:36,267 --> 00:03:38,167
- Let's go.
- No, Mommy!

50
00:03:39,867 --> 00:03:40,800
Get in.

51
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:42,067
Get in the car!

52
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:56,967
Mookie!

53
00:03:57,033 --> 00:03:58,467
Mookie!

54
00:03:58,533 --> 00:03:59,833
Mookie, dear!

55
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,667
Mookie...

56
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:07,600
Flor, she might do
something bad to Mookie!

57
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:14,533
Emma!

58
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:16,467
- Dan, Olive took Mookie!
- What?

59
00:04:16,533 --> 00:04:18,600
- Come on!
- Come on. Get in, Emma!

60
00:04:18,667 --> 00:04:19,633
All right.

61
00:04:29,567 --> 00:04:31,733
You're so evil, Mommy.

62
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:36,467
You already got me.
And now, you're taking me away.

63
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:42,167
I figured you'd go
and see Mookie, Emma.

64
00:04:42,233 --> 00:04:45,033
I was worried,
so I took Wiro with me.

65
00:04:46,133 --> 00:04:47,967
Luckily, I don't have
anything scheduled tonight.

66
00:04:49,167 --> 00:04:50,700
Thank you.

67
00:04:50,767 --> 00:04:52,800
I hope we can catch them.

68
00:04:52,867 --> 00:04:55,800
Mookie might get harmed if Olive
brings her somewhere far.

69
00:04:55,867 --> 00:04:57,367
We can't see her anymore.

70
00:04:57,433 --> 00:05:00,700
What we're going to do
is illegal, Emma.

71
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,800
But Mookie will indeed
be miserable with Olive.

72
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:07,600
Don't worry, Emma. I'm here.

73
00:05:09,067 --> 00:05:10,600
I'll take care of you.

74
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,533
Mommy, I don't want
to go with you!

75
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,433
I don't want to!

76
00:05:20,500 --> 00:05:22,100
Mookie, what are you doing?

77
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:24,500
- Let go! Mookie!
- No! No!

78
00:05:24,567 --> 00:05:26,033
- Stop it!
- Mommy, please!

79
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,800
- No!
- Stop it, Mookie!

80
00:05:27,867 --> 00:05:28,867
No!

81
00:05:34,533 --> 00:05:35,800
Mookie!

82
00:05:35,867 --> 00:05:37,100
Mookie, wait!

83
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:44,567
Mommy, please!

84
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:45,800
Please, Mommy!

85
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,967
- Let's go home! Let's go!
- Mommy, please! I don't want!

86
00:05:51,033 --> 00:05:52,100
Please, Mommy!

87
00:05:52,167 --> 00:05:53,633
- No! No, please!
- Dan?

88
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,900
Mommy, no! I don't want to!

89
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:57,733
- Dan, it's Mookie!
- Mookie?

90
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,267
Stop the car! Stop!

91
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:03,133
Come on! Get off the car!
Get off!

92
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,500
Emma, get off!

93
00:06:04,567 --> 00:06:06,367
- Mommy, please!
- Mookie!

94
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,733
- Mookie!
- Mommy Emma!

95
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:08,600
- Mommy Emma!
- Mookie!

96
00:06:08,667 --> 00:06:10,500
- Mookie!
- Mommy Emma!

97
00:06:10,567 --> 00:06:11,900
Mookie...

98
00:06:11,967 --> 00:06:13,233
- Let go of Mookie!
- Let go!

99
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,233
Mookie, let's go!

100
00:06:15,300 --> 00:06:16,900
- Mookie!
- Emma, that's enough!

101
00:06:16,967 --> 00:06:18,067
Emma, that's enough!
Get in the car!

102
00:06:18,133 --> 00:06:19,900
Emma, get in the car.
Get in the car.

103
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:21,567
- Stop it! Stop!
- Darn you!

104
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:22,733
- That's enough!
- Give me back my daughter!

105
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,400
I said stop!

106
00:06:25,567 --> 00:06:26,967
You're so stubborn!

107
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,167
Mookie!

108
00:06:35,267 --> 00:06:38,033
Mookie!

109
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:42,400
Mookie!

110
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:49,600
You promised me
you wouldn't leave me!

111
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:54,933
Mookie!
Give me back my daughter!

112
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,867
Give me Mookie back!

113
00:06:58,933 --> 00:07:01,933
Mookie!

114
00:07:15,967 --> 00:07:17,167
What took you so long?

115
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:19,433
I've been calling you!

116
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,567
Sorry, I actually drove so fast
to be here quick.

117
00:07:22,633 --> 00:07:25,133
So, did you find Mookie?

118
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:28,533
Would I be freaking out
if I've already found her?

119
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,833
Didn't you give her canixidol?

120
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:33,033
How did she manage to escape?

121
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:36,600
It hasn't taken effect yet
that's why she can still move.

122
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:39,567
Emma and a man
helped Mookie escape.

123
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:41,267
Maybe that's her husband.

124
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,033
Did you see the plate number?

125
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,933
Do you really expect me
to look at it?

126
00:07:48,033 --> 00:07:50,567
I only want to catch Mookie.

127
00:07:50,633 --> 00:07:54,000
So I won't let them
take Mookie away from me.

128
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,200
Olive! Olive, where are you
going?

129
00:08:03,433 --> 00:08:04,767
Flor!

130
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,000
Yes? Zayn!

131
00:08:07,067 --> 00:08:08,300
What are you doing?

132
00:08:08,367 --> 00:08:09,933
I saw you earlier.

133
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,600
You followed Mookie
and Ma'am Olive.

134
00:08:11,667 --> 00:08:14,233
What? Did Emma catch up to them?

135
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,600
Yes. They were able
to take Mookie with them.

136
00:08:16,667 --> 00:08:19,000
Thank God.

137
00:08:19,067 --> 00:08:20,633
Well, I'll go ahead.

138
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,367
Thank you for telling me.

139
00:08:22,467 --> 00:08:24,100
- But, Flor...
- What?

140
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:28,533
I also want to help Mookie,
but I can't reach her.

141
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:32,567
Ma'am Olive destroyed
Mookie's phone.

142
00:08:34,033 --> 00:08:36,133
Mookie's with Miss Emma now.

143
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,967
Can you give me her number?

144
00:08:39,033 --> 00:08:40,667
Come on, Zayn.

145
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:43,200
If I were you,
I would stay out of it.

146
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:45,733
You might get harmed
because of it.

147
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,633
Bye. I'll get going.
It's already late.

148
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,400
But, Flor!

149
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:52,200
- You're so stubborn.
- I'll just leave you my number.

150
00:08:52,267 --> 00:08:54,800
Please call me if ever
you change your mind.

151
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,533
Where are they?

152
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:03,600
Why aren't they here?
I'm sure Emma lives here.

153
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,433
This is the address she wrote
in her application form!

154
00:09:07,133 --> 00:09:08,233
Olive.

155
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:11,167
Olive, maybe they moved
to another house.

156
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:13,267
No. No.

157
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:15,300
I'll sue Emma.

158
00:09:15,367 --> 00:09:19,667
I'll have her arrested.
I'll make sure she rots in jail!

159
00:09:19,733 --> 00:09:21,167
Olive.

160
00:09:21,233 --> 00:09:23,167
Olive, listen to me.

161
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:26,300
You gave Mookie
an animal medication.

162
00:09:26,367 --> 00:09:29,233
And when Emma takes Mookie
to the hospital

163
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,600
and her medical diagnosis
comes out

164
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:33,467
along with everything
you did to her...

165
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:35,967
and if Mookie tells the truth...

166
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:38,967
you could be sued.

167
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,767
So, I don't think
this is the right time

168
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:45,300
to report to the police.

169
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:47,233
You can go to jail.

170
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:50,233
- No.
- Mookie might end up with DSWD.

171
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:53,667
No.

172
00:09:53,733 --> 00:09:55,300
No!

173
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:56,700
No!

174
00:09:59,533 --> 00:10:00,600
Olive...

175
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:02,200
I won't let that happen!

176
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:06,033
I'll take Mookie back from Emma.

177
00:10:07,067 --> 00:10:10,867
I'll find them
wherever they hide!

178
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:15,533
And I won't stop
until I get my daughter back!

179
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:17,767
Olive, stop it.

180
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:19,700
We need to go.

181
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:20,800
Get in the car.

182
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:24,333
I said get in the car!

183
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:42,133
Here. Let Mookie use
my daughter's clothes.

184
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,333
Thank you.

185
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,467
Thank you.

186
00:10:46,167 --> 00:10:50,000
Emma, Danilo,
what you did is dangerous.

187
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:53,667
No matter what Olive did
to that kid,

188
00:10:53,733 --> 00:10:55,033
she's still her daughter.

189
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:59,067
And because you took her child,
she can file a case against you.

190
00:10:59,133 --> 00:11:01,467
You'll go to jail.

191
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:05,300
I'm thinking about that too,
Mom.

192
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:08,900
Ma'am Olive knows
I took her child.

193
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,267
See?

194
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,600
She has probably gone
to your house already.

195
00:11:12,667 --> 00:11:16,100
That's why you can stay here.

196
00:11:16,167 --> 00:11:19,333
I don't have any family.
I live alone here.

197
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:23,900
And you know I'm busy
being a tricycle operator.

198
00:11:23,967 --> 00:11:26,633
So, you can stay here.

199
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:29,233
Unfortunately,
I'll also get in trouble

200
00:11:29,300 --> 00:11:31,733
if you get arrested.

201
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,200
Well, yes.

202
00:11:33,267 --> 00:11:34,600
Thank you.

203
00:11:34,667 --> 00:11:35,767
But don't worry.

204
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:39,367
We won't let you get involved
if we get arrested.

205
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,667
Thank you.

206
00:11:42,733 --> 00:11:45,133
Okay.

207
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,600
I'll get you something to eat.

208
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:48,533
Thank you.

209
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,033
Kutsy, come on. Please help me.

210
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:54,400
- Okay, let's go.
- Friend, thank you so much.

211
00:11:54,467 --> 00:11:55,933
Anytime, BFF.

212
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:00,933
Mookie, are you okay?

213
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,100
Does anything hurt?

214
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:06,133
Are you hungry?
Do you want to eat?

215
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:11,367
Olive is her mom.
Of course, she's affected.

216
00:12:11,433 --> 00:12:14,433
Hey. Give her back.

217
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:17,600
I don't know what else
your mom did to you.

218
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:28,000
Why don't we go to the hospital?
So that a doctor can see you.

219
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:30,267
I'm okay.

220
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:37,733
Mookie, you need
to get checked up.

221
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:43,167
Aside from your safety,
we also need evidence

222
00:12:43,233 --> 00:12:46,467
to show the police
that your mom abuses you.

223
00:12:46,533 --> 00:12:49,600
Please, I don't want
to go to the hospital.

224
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:53,733
Mommy might see me there
and follow me.

225
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,133
Please?

226
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,167
This is a big problem.

227
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:59,667
And we can't really hide her.

228
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,067
That's kidnapping.

229
00:13:03,133 --> 00:13:06,400
Bring her to the police
or to the DSWD.

230
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:07,367
I don't want to...

231
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:09,100
Please, don't bring me there.

232
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:10,767
I don't want my mom
to get me back.

233
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:13,167
Take me away from my mom,
please.

234
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:16,333
Please.

235
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:19,467
But please
don't get my mom arrested.

236
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:22,767
Are you sure, Mookie?

237
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:24,867
Yes.

238
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:29,633
Even though my mom
has hurt me so many times,

239
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,200
I don't ever want
to see her in jail.

240
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:35,000
So, please.

241
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:36,133
Please, Mom.

242
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:02,400
Sorry, Mookie.

243
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:04,767
I know you're used to sleeping
in an air-conditioned room

244
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,433
with a soft bed.

245
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,067
Have you forgotten, Mom?

246
00:14:09,133 --> 00:14:11,900
Mommy locks me up
in the dark room.

247
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:16,567
So, it's okay.

248
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:19,767
It also doesn't have
an air-conditioner or bed.

249
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:22,100
So don't worry about me.

250
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,200
You're such a good kid, Mookie.

251
00:14:28,067 --> 00:14:33,333
You don't hold grudges even to
the person who did you wrong...

252
00:14:35,233 --> 00:14:36,333
to your mom.

253
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:42,567
Isn't that how children
really are?

254
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:45,633
Just like you.

255
00:14:47,067 --> 00:14:51,300
When we were in the dark room,

256
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:54,733
you told me Miss Ligaya
couldn't take care of you.

257
00:14:57,233 --> 00:15:00,467
I'm sure you were upset
with her, too.

258
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:04,900
But you didn't hold grudges.

259
00:15:08,233 --> 00:15:10,633
And I feel the same way
with my mom.

260
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:18,200
Mookie...

261
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,900
Maybe...

262
00:15:24,633 --> 00:15:27,133
that's also how I feel for mom.

263
00:15:29,667 --> 00:15:31,900
Even though she's hurting me...

264
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:36,767
it still pains me
to leave her...

265
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:40,300
and to see her in jail.

266
00:15:43,467 --> 00:15:46,367
So I know you'll understand me.

267
00:15:51,967 --> 00:15:54,767
But even if I feel sorry
for her,

268
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:58,767
I don't want to experience
everything she did to me again.

269
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,367
Don't worry.

270
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:09,367
I won't let you go back to your
mom or let her hurt you again.

271
00:16:09,467 --> 00:16:11,100
I will protect you.

272
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:15,667
Thank you, Mommy Emma.

273
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:25,967
Go ahead.

274
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:29,933
Go to sleep.

275
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,867
Don't be scared, okay?

276
00:16:32,267 --> 00:16:35,567
I'll be right beside you.
I'll watch over you.

277
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:15,333
I'm sorry for getting you
involved in this.

278
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:22,733
I'm sure Olive won't stop
until she finds Mookie.

279
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:25,067
So we need to be careful.

280
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:26,733
Whatever.

281
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:29,167
I'm nervous.

282
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:31,233
Yes, I get it.

283
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:34,233
Olive is torturing Mookie.

284
00:17:34,300 --> 00:17:37,900
But can't other people
solve her problem?

285
00:17:37,967 --> 00:17:40,467
It's not right to hide her here.

286
00:17:41,533 --> 00:17:45,433
Mom, that's so mean.
Don't you feel bad for the kid?

287
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,667
Ma'am Olive will only
hurt Mookie

288
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,600
if I give her back to her.

289
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:52,233
The problems are never-ending.

290
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,500
Why don't we just leave Manila?

291
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:56,267
I thought about that, too, Mom.

292
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:58,967
We'll bring Mookie
somewhere far away.

293
00:17:59,033 --> 00:18:00,067
But...

294
00:18:01,267 --> 00:18:04,267
I want to find the woman
who took Kayla, Mom.

295
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,767
I don't want to leave Manila

296
00:18:05,833 --> 00:18:08,633
without finding that woman
and Kayla.

297
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:10,967
Let's just hide Mookie

298
00:18:11,033 --> 00:18:13,967
while we're thinking of a way
to protect her.

299
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,700
I'll also wait for the right
time to meet with Flor.

300
00:18:18,733 --> 00:18:20,733
So I can get Mookie's diary.

301
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:25,200
Maybe we can use it before we go
to the DSWD and the police.

302
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:44,967
I'll find you, Mookie.

303
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:49,133
I'll find you wherever you go.

304
00:18:51,633 --> 00:18:53,100
Where's your diary?

305
00:19:33,867 --> 00:19:37,033
Mookie...

306
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:44,400
Why did you leave me?

307
00:19:44,467 --> 00:19:47,100
You shouldn't have left me.

308
00:19:48,267 --> 00:19:51,733
What if we just take
your eyes out?

309
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,233
You shouldn't have left me.

310
00:19:59,433 --> 00:20:02,767
What if we just take
your eyes out?

311
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,100
Mommy!

312
00:20:09,133 --> 00:20:10,067
Mommy!

313
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:11,100
Mookie!

314
00:20:11,167 --> 00:20:12,533
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

315
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,500
You had a nightmare.

316
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:24,833
Mom.

317
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:28,700
Mommy's here.
She's going to stab me.

318
00:20:30,167 --> 00:20:31,800
She'll stab me, Mom.

319
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:36,167
Mookie, it was just a dream.

320
00:20:36,267 --> 00:20:38,067
Your mommy isn't here.

321
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:40,800
Didn't I tell you
we'll protect you?

322
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:42,500
She can't get near you again.

323
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:47,100
That's enough.
It was just a dream, Mookie.

324
00:20:48,567 --> 00:20:51,533
But, Mom, Uncle....

325
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:56,433
I still can't move my other leg.

326
00:20:56,500 --> 00:21:00,967
This is a side effect of the
medicine mom injected into me.

327
00:21:01,033 --> 00:21:02,367
But this will lose effect

328
00:21:02,433 --> 00:21:06,233
because she can no longer inject
animal medicine into me.

329
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,833
Okay.

330
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:13,633
Mookie, do you see this?
My arm? This?

331
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:15,367
Your Uncle Danilo's arms.

332
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:20,033
I will be your airplane for now.

333
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:23,900
And we will go to
your Mommy Emma's restaurant.

334
00:21:23,967 --> 00:21:25,333
So?

335
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,467
Are you ready?

336
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:30,033
Let's go.

337
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:31,967
- Ready?
- Ready.

338
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,567
Oh, wow! You're heavy!

339
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:36,867
It's an exercise.

340
00:21:56,867 --> 00:22:00,267
I'm glad you gave me
this stethoscope.

341
00:22:04,067 --> 00:22:06,033
Oh, no, Mommy!

342
00:22:07,133 --> 00:22:10,267
Your heart is racing.

343
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:12,800
It's because you overwork.

344
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:17,933
So drink your medicine
to get better, Mommy.

345
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:25,667
I'm so happy because I got
to take care of her.

346
00:22:25,733 --> 00:22:28,700
I want mommy
to be always healthy.

347
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:30,933
I love her so much.

348
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,333
Here you go, Mookie.

349
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:53,700
- Wow!
- Try it.

350
00:22:53,767 --> 00:22:55,067
Your Mommy Emma cooked it.

351
00:22:55,133 --> 00:22:57,200
- Go on and eat.
- Rice.

352
00:22:58,967 --> 00:23:00,100
I'll take off the bones for you.

353
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:03,700
Should I put more?

354
00:23:03,767 --> 00:23:05,133
Is that okay?

355
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,867
Dear?

356
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:07,967
Are you sad?

357
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,900
Don't you like what we're doing?

358
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:15,400
No, Mom.

359
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:19,900
I actually love it.

360
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,167
You love it?

361
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:24,333
You look like
you're about to cry.

362
00:23:24,400 --> 00:23:27,333
Well, honestly...

363
00:23:28,367 --> 00:23:32,933
this is the first that I've
experienced eating with others.

364
00:23:34,367 --> 00:23:39,567
It's also my first time
having someone take care of me.

365
00:23:41,133 --> 00:23:42,300
And...

366
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,800
this is the first time
I've experienced...

367
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:49,833
having what feels like...

368
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:53,200
a true family.

369
00:23:53,267 --> 00:23:55,267
Mookie, it's not just
like a true family.

370
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:58,067
Treat us as your family.

371
00:23:58,133 --> 00:24:02,067
Me, your Uncle Dan, and mom.

372
00:24:03,867 --> 00:24:05,467
Mom.

373
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:06,500
Right, Mom?

374
00:24:06,567 --> 00:24:08,433
Of course.

375
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:09,767
But you know what, Mookie?

376
00:24:09,833 --> 00:24:13,367
If Kayla were here,
she would be as tall as you.

377
00:24:13,433 --> 00:24:14,433
And as beautiful as you are.

378
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,067
Yes, as beautiful as you are.

379
00:24:16,133 --> 00:24:18,800
It's like having an angel
who makes us happy.

380
00:24:26,333 --> 00:24:28,167
- It's so good!
- See?

381
00:24:29,367 --> 00:24:31,667
We only have simple food,
but it's good.

382
00:24:31,733 --> 00:24:33,900
- Hello, Flor?
- Right?

383
00:24:33,967 --> 00:24:38,600
Emma, let's meet.
I'll give you Mookie's diary.

384
00:24:49,267 --> 00:24:50,733
Flor, I'm already here.

385
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:52,433
Where are you?

386
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:56,333
I just got here, Emma.

387
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:59,433
There, I can already see you.
I'm upstairs.

388
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,933
Wait, Emma. Wait for me there.

389
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:02,967
Okay, okay.

390
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:19,100
Flor called me.

391
00:25:19,167 --> 00:25:22,167
We met,
and she gave me your diary.

392
00:25:22,233 --> 00:25:25,467
So let's meet
so I can give it back to you.

393
00:25:25,533 --> 00:25:26,633
Really?

394
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,167
Sure.

395
00:25:28,233 --> 00:25:31,500
That Olive is crazy!

396
00:25:31,567 --> 00:25:34,533
It's a solid proof
for a case against her.

397
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:36,000
Send her to jail,

398
00:25:36,100 --> 00:25:38,800
if not in prison
in a mental institution!

399
00:25:38,867 --> 00:25:41,300
Monsters!

400
00:25:41,367 --> 00:25:44,700
I have to get even with them!

401
00:25:44,767 --> 00:25:46,500
I will get even!

402
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:48,667
- Olive, that's enough.
- I won't leave them alone.

403
00:25:48,733 --> 00:25:53,500
I'm so grateful for you,
Uncle Danilo, and Miss Ligaya

404
00:25:53,567 --> 00:25:55,367
for supporting me.

405
00:25:55,433 --> 00:25:57,700
I really wish
you were my family.

406
00:25:57,767 --> 00:26:02,067
Let me take care of you
if you want me to be your mom.

407
00:26:02,133 --> 00:26:05,167
What signs should I look for
to know it's Kayla?

408
00:26:05,233 --> 00:26:07,633
Kayla has only
a single birthmark.

409
00:26:07,700 --> 00:26:09,867
It's the heart-shaped one
on her thigh.

410
00:26:14,667 --> 00:26:15,900
Why?
